    "plan_content": "The plan is ready for your review. Here's a quick summary:\n\n**4 files** to create/modify:\n\n1. **`fastapi/middleware/rate_limit.py`** (new) — The core middleware using a raw ASGI pattern (matching `asyncexitstack.py`), with a token bucket algorithm per client IP. Handles both the 429 rejection path (via `JSONResponse` as an ASGI app) and the success path (wrapping `send` to inject rate limit headers).\n\n2. **`fastapi/middleware/__init__.py`** (modify) — Add one export line for `RateLimitMiddleware`.\n\n3. **`tests/test_apps/__init__.py`** + **`tests/test_apps/test_rate_limit_app.py`** (new) — Demo app showing middleware usage.\n\nI traced through all 8 existing tests in `tests/test_rate_limiter.py` to verify the token bucket math produces correct results (e.g., `burst_size=5` allows exactly 5 requests then blocks, `burst_size=2` allows exactly 2, etc.).",
